Name: Feminist Justice Coalition
Short description: Feminist Justice Coalition (FJC) is about creating feminist community, fostering conversation, engaging in advocacy and providing opportunities for education on campus. FJC provides western students an opportunity to interact with like-minded individuals oriented towards intersectional feminist ideals. FJC strives to provide students with a safer space to explore and learn and engage with new and familiar feminist topics. In this way, FJC is committed to anti-oppressive practice and the ongoing work of providing safer spaces and accessible spaces. As a club with a coalitional approach, FJC is concerned with focusing on specific issues and building our communities capacity to support one another and take action. We are not concerned with individual?s identity as a requisite for club participation, FJC welcomes and encourages all Western students to reach out, interact and participate in club activities. Within an intersectional feminist lens, FJC is committed to reproductive justice advocacy on the Western campus. FJC recognizes that reproductive justice is grounded in the politic that the creation of a family is a human right, encompassing other human rights such as a safe and clean environment, clean drinking water, community, bodily autonomy, choice and education. Have more questions? Find us on social media at Feminist Justice Coalition or email us!

Name: Friends of MSF (Medecin Sans Frontieres)

Name: Health Occupation Students of America Western

HOSA Western aims to help students become more open to different careers related to health sciences. There are hundreds of possibilities for a career in healthcare or medicine, yet sadly many of these options are not even considered by students. HOSA Western hopes to create a safe place for all science students to engage their interests. The club will hold weekly workshops where club members will be guided through various healthcare-related skills and topics by students who are not professionals but have previous experience with the HOSA competition. They have experience preparing for the Spring Leadership Conference (National Competition) and the International Leadership Conference (International Competition).

Name: Heart and Stroke Club

Name: Black Students' Association

Name: Breakers

Name: Choir

Name: Dance Force

Name: Humanitarian Society (previously Western Red Cross)

We provide our members with a wide variety of regular volunteer opportunities within the London community. We will also be offering First Aid courses for discounted prices to our members. Our goal is to instill in the UWO community the fundamental principles of the International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement: Humanity, Impartiality, Neutrality, Independence, Voluntary Service, Unity and Universality.

Name: Marine Biology Society

Name: Pre-Dental Society

We aim to act as a social platform, resource bank, and lifelong mentor for students through events, presentations, and competitions.

Name: Western Foodies
Short description: The purpose of Western Foodies (previously The Kitchen and Dining Room Club) is to bring students together who share a passion and appreciation for good food and drink in a social setting.

Name: Western for Ooch
Short description: Western for Ooch is a student-run club affiliated with Camp Oochigeas, a camp for children with cancer

Name: Western for the Elderly
Short description: The objective of Western for the Elderly will be to connect Western students with London?s elderly population in hopes to unite the two in sharing ideas, attending events and forming friendships.

Name: Western Forex Association
Short description: The Western Forex Association (WFA) is a UWO USC ratified organization which aims to raise awareness about and spark a deep interest in the Forex market.

Name: Western Founders Network
Short description: Western Founders Network is the central hub for aspiring tech entrepreneurs on campus. Our mission is to foster innovation on campus by giving students the knowhow and the means to develop, establish, and grow their unique startup ventures.

Name: Western French Club
Short description: The French Club aims to promote the French language and Francophone cultures through fun social events, conversation hours, newsletters, academic support, team sports and more! Worried about your French skills?

Name: Western Graphics Club
Short description: We are aiming to bring together a community of aspiring graphic designers on campus! We host workshops to learn about graphic design, networking events and socials to get connected. No previous experience in graphic design is required.

Name: Charity Chords
Short description: Yo! Welcome to Westerns Guitar Club!

Name: Western Hockey Community
Short description: This is a club for students to gather and embrace the sport of hockey.

Name: Western Investment Club
Short description: The Western Investment Club ("WIC")'s mandate is to spark interest in young investors, and teach the fundamentals of value investing. The club manages over $180,000 of real capital in a diversified portfolio of U.S. and Canadian equities.

Name: Western Jugglers Club
Short description: The award winning Western Juggling Club is a student club that promotes juggling as a fun, stress-relieving activity that helps develop hand-eye coordination. The club is suitable for jugglers of all skill levels
Tags: Hobbies/ Special Interests,Music and Performing Arts

Name: Western Liberals
Short description: The purpose of the club is to support local liberal candidates, both the federal and provincial liberal parties as well as the Ontario young liberals and the young liberals of Canada. We are also a social club and hold many events, bring in speakers and travel to a variety of political conferences nation wide!

Name: Western Lifeline
Short description: Western Lifeline is the pro-life presence at UWO. We believe in human rights for all human beings. Our mission is to make abortion unthinkable on our campus.

Name: Western Magic: The Gathering Association
Short description: The Magic: The Gathering Trading Card Game club at Western. We welcome both casual and competitive players. Weekly meetings with drafts, tournaments etc.

Name: Western Marketing Association
Short description: The objective of this club is to unite Western students interested in marketing and provide them with resources that will help better their skill sin the marketing stream of their choice.

Name: Western Meal Exchange
Short description: Meal Exchange, a Canadian charity, focuses on food sustainability and local hunger.

Name: Western Model United Nations Society
Short description: We debate, discuss and learn more about various issues around the world in the spirit of the United Nations.

Name: Western Ontario Organization of Filipinos
Short description: Social/Cultural Club:WOOF sets out to act as Cultural Ambassadors of the Filipino Culture on the UWO campus. Our mission is to construct an outlet for Filipino Arts both traditional and contemporary.

Name: Western Photography Club
Short description: Want to be a part of a group of passionate photographers? Western Photography Club is the perfect fit for all levels of shutterbugs. We run tutorials, socials and even give you the opportunity to shoot University Events and Concerts. Join us today!

Name: Western Piano Society
Short description: Interested in piano or music in general? Join the Western Piano Society! ANYONE of any skill level (even no skill) is welcome! We hold concerts, offer piano lessons and volunteer as musicians in the community.

Name: Western Pre Law Society
Short description: The Pre-Law Society is an academic club for those who are interested in pursuing a career in the field of Law. The club provides speakers and events geared towards helping our members gain entrance into the law school of their choice.

Name: Western Psychology Association
Short description: The WPA is for any student with an interest in psychology. We hold social, academic, and volunteer events, and are always looking for enthusiastic members to participate! If you're a psych student at Western, the WPA is your best possible resource.

Name: Western Punjabi Association
Short description: Western Punjabi Association is a cultural club representing the Punjabi culture here at Western.

Name: Western Real Estate Club
Short description: The Western Estate Club (WREC) is the only real estate club at Western University which is accessible to all Western University students

Name: Western Sign Language Club
Short description: The Western Sign Language Club is a group of people that meet to learn American Sign Language together.

Name: Western Sikh Students Association
Short description: A friendly environment for Sikh students to come together, attend various social events and be involved in the community. Discussion about religion, spirituality, and world events are also encouraged.

Name: Western Soccer Association
Short description: The Western Soccer Association strives to hit on every facet of the beautiful game to provide members with the best all-around experience. This ranges from numerous playing opportunities to watching games at the Spoke, and everything in between!

Name: Western Sport Business Club
Short description: The Western Sport Business Club (WSBC) is a student organization with the purpose of bringing together students with a particular interest in the sport business industry. Join us for networking opportunities, speaker series, facility tours and more.

Name: Western Sports Analytics Club
Short description: The Western Sports Analytics Club aims to provide students with opportunities to grow and apply their passion in Sports Analytics through workshops, speakers, networking events and meetings. Students of all levels of exposure to Sports Analytics are encouraged to join as events will be suited to varying degrees of experience.

Name: Western Stem Cell Club
Short description: WSSC aims to improve the quality and quantity of membership on Canada?s stem cell donor database by organizing and running stem cell drives on campus and around London.

Name: Western Strength
Short description: Western Strength is a friendly community of lifters dedicated to democratizing strength training and sharing athletic, nutritional, and scientific theory & practice.

Name: Western Transport Advocacy Association
Short description: We are a club meant to gather together like-minded transit enthusiasts at Western. We aim to promote the development and advocacy of issues surrounding transit, infrastructure and mobility in general through exciting activities, debates and discussion in our community.

Name: Western Trivia Club
Short description: Western Trivia Club is all about playing various forms of trivia. Quizbowl tournaments are our main challenge, but we enjoy trivia in many forms and on many topics. All are welcome, regardless of expertise or experience.

Name: Western Ukrainian Students Club
Short description: Meet other Ukrainians that attend the University of Western Ontario and be a part of London's Ukrainian community. Get in touch with your heritage!

Name: Western University Korean Student Association
Short description: Western University Korean Students' Association (WUKSA) is a club that strives to create a forum for all Korean students and anyone interested in Korean culture, across all faculties and undergraduate student bodies.

Name: Western University Lebanese Students Association
Short description: The club aims to promote and educate the student body about the Lebanese society and culture. This club is committed to establishing a voice for the Lebanese students at Western University.?

Name: Western University Politics, Philosophy and Economics
Short description: The Western PPE society is intended to provide students pursuing studies in PPE the chance to meet other students and faculty from the various disciplines captured by the program. The PPE Society will be able to offer its members a close community of like-minded students and exposure to some of the more interesting topics being discussed in the faculties of economics, politics, and philosophy.

Name: Western University Technology Review
Short description: The Western University Technology Review (WUTR) publishes articles that inform readers about the technological advancements that shape our lives and examine the nature in which they do so.

Name: Western University Vegan Society
Short description: The Western University Vegan Society is an inclusive community working towards a peaceful world, free from violence and discrimination towards all animals - human and non.

Name: Western Venture Association
Short description: The Western Venture Association aims to increase awareness in venture capital and private equity by providing students with educationals, speaker events and case competitions at Western University.

Name: Western Vietnamese Student Association
Short description: The Vietnamese Students' Association is an organization created to promote Vietnamese Culture, to develop social networks and to strengthen the relationship between the Vietnamese community at the University of Western Ontario

Name: Western Wildlife Conservation Society
Short description: The purpose of the Western Wildlife Conservation Society is to raise awareness about a healthy, diverse, and ultimately sustainable living Earth.

Name: Western Women in Leadership
Short description: WWIL is a new club that desires to motivate young women at the University of Western Ontario toward embracing leadership roles and pursuing success.

Name: Western Women in STEM
Short description: Women in Stem focuses on the professional development of our members in STEM fields.

Name: Western's Indo-Canadian Students' Association (WICSA)
Short description: WICSA is Western's biggest South Asian organization, established in 1983. We are dedicated to providing a our members with a variety of experiences and events, while celebrating our culture and cultivating a strong sense of community.

Name: WesternU Conservatives
Short description: This year is a very exciting time to be a Conservative. There is a vast array of Club events that we put on including: socials, policy events, meeting with key politicians, Model Parliament and election campaigning.

Name: Women in Fitness
Short description: Women in Fitness (WIF) is an organization for Western students who identify as a woman who have a passion for physical fitness and healthy eating. The goal of WIF is to motivate, educate, and encourage its members in their fitness journey to be the healthiest they can be through exercise, food and community.?

Name: WUSC
Short description: Are you interested in international development, humanitarian issues, education for a more equitable world, helping out in your London community, and helping out the world? If so, join WUSC!

Name: Young Tutors
Short description: The Western Young Tutors provide students throughout the London area with affordable, quality tutoring services to high school and post-secondary students in the London community.

Name: Zua Western
Short description: Zua Western is committed to educating students about the power of using financial tools and technologies in creating a significant social impact as well as exposing them to the various methods by which non-profits and social enterprises can help to alleviate poverty and effect positive change in the global economy.?

Name: Caribbean Students' Organization (CSO)
Short description: The Caribbean Student's Organization provides a home away from home for those of Caribbean descent and works towards the enhancement of Western's knowledge of Caribbean culture.

Name: Crohn's and Colitis Club of Western
Short description: The Crohn?s and Colitis Club of Western aims to raise awareness for Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD) and provide students with the opportunity to share their experiences and learn more about Crohn?s disease and Colitis

Name: Envelope for Joy
Short description: Our aim is to spread positivity within the university, London, and international communities through hand-written letters and cards.

Name: Muslim Students' Association
Short description: The Muslim Students' Association (MSA) is one of the largest clubs on campus. The mission of the MSA is to provide an Islamic environment conducive to creativity, leadership, excellence and professionalism to empower students to reach their potential

Name: Pre-Medical Society
Short description: The UWO Pre-Medical Society encourages interest in the medical profession through academic and social programming as well as by providing community and medically-related volunteer opportunities in London and overseas.

Name: Swing Kids
Short description: Fun loving group who meet once a week to Lindy Hop, East Coast and Charleston! Men AND women welcome, and absolutely no experience necessary. Join us for a fabulous time, smile until your cheeks hurt and let some swingin tunes move your feet!
